d can affect different parts of the body. Common manifestations of lupus include skin rashes (such as the characteristic butterfly rash), joint pain and swelling, fatigue, fever, and organ involvement, such as the kidneys, heart, lungs, or brain.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-1311_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-1312_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-1313_">Illuminating Lupus - Delving into the disease</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/male-shin-with-redness-and-itchy-rash-on-skin-2023-11-27-05-11-12-utc.jpg?v=1709047268" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/male-shin-with-redness-and-itchy-rash-on-skin-2023-11-27-05-11-12-utc.jpg?v=1709047268 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/male-shin-with-redness-and-itchy-rash-on-skin-2023-11-27-05-11-12-utc_1000x.jpg?v=1709047268 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/male-shin-with-redness-and-itchy-rash-on-skin-2023-11-27-05-11-12-utc_500x.jpg?v=1709047268 320w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Uniting Against Lupus: Raising Awareness on World Lupus Day - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Uniting Against Lupus: Raising Awareness on World Lupus Day - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-1315_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-1316_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by vvoennyy via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-1318_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">This segment delves deep into the essence of lupus, a complex autoimmune disorder characterised by the immune system mistakenly attacking its own tissues. It sheds light on the wide array of symptoms that lupus can manifest, from joint pain and fatigue to severe organ damage, highlighting the unpredictable nature of the disease. The role of the immune system, central to the condition, is explored in detail, providing insights into how its misdirection leads to the diverse clinical presentations of lupus. By unravelling the intricacies of lupus, this guide aims to demystify the condition, offering clarity and understanding to those it affects and the broader community.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-1320_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-1321_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-1322_">How World Lupus Day engages readers</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/awareness-2023-11-27-05-24-40-utc.jpg?v=1709047377" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/awareness-2023-11-27-05-24-40-utc.jpg?v=1709047377 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/awareness-2023-11-27-05-24-40-utc_1000x.jpg?v=1709047377 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/awareness-2023-11-27-05-24-40-utc_500x.jpg?v=1709047377 320w" width="1000" height="750" alt="Exploring Lupus: Understanding the Complexities of Autoimmune Disease - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Exploring Lupus: Understanding the Complexities of Autoimmune Disease - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-1324_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-1325_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by wanaktek via Envato Elements</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-1327_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-1328_"><b>Raising awareness</b> - World Lupus Day provides an opportunity to educate the public about lupus, its symptoms, and its impact on individuals' lives. Learners can engage with informative resources, events, and social media campaigns to increase their understanding of the disease.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-1330_"><b>Supporting patients</b> - Learners can explore resources from organisations such as Lupus UK, the World Lupus Federation, the Lupus Foundation of America, and The Mandatory Training Group to support individuals living with lupus. These organisations offer a wealth of information, support services, and advocacy efforts to improve the lives of those affected by the disease.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-1332_"><b>Advocacy and research</b> - By participating in World Lupus Day activities, learners can contribute to advocacy and fundraising efforts to support lupus research. Increased funding for research can lead to better treatments, improved diagnostic tools, and ultimately, a better quality of life for individuals with lupus.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-1334_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-1335_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-1336_">Key facts and statistics</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_3d527365-e6e0-4ae8-8fef-e7dbba0f7ff3.png?v=1709045105" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_3d527365-e6e0-4ae8-8fef-e7dbba0f7ff3.png?v=1709045105 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_3d527365-e6e0-4ae8-8fef-e7dbba0f7ff3_1000x.png?v=1709045105 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_3d527365-e6e0-4ae8-8fef-e7dbba0f7ff3_500x.png?v=1709045105 320w" width="1419" height="946" alt="3.png__PID:08ff5d47-d516-4440-b42c-f3f83109d406" title="Unveiling the rainbow: Exploring the history and meaning of Pride Month - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-1338_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-1339_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by mohdizzuanbinroslan via Envato Elements</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-1341_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-1342_">Lupus affects approximately 5 million people worldwide, with 90% of cases occurring in women, primarily between the ages of 15 and 44.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-1344_">Despite its prevalence, lupus remains challenging to diagnose, with an average time to diagnosis of 6 years.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-1346_">Lupus can affect any organ or system in the body, leading to a wide range of symptoms, including fatigue, joint pain, skin rashes, and organ damage.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-1348_">There is currently no cure for lupus, but early diagnosis and appropriate treatment can help manage symptoms and improve quality of life.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-1350_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-1351_"><h3 tabindex=